{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VjTko1AurzxioVsEtqJP4s","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9d3ab825-6dfa-42d3-92d1-28b7bc09852d","uuid":"42b21359-13c3-4451-b393-4ef9d44e6e60","timestamp":"2026-03-23T08:35:54.844Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","oldString":"- **AC7 indirect:** Test source files not shipped in npm package, so vitest/bats couldn't run in container. Verified indirectly via all 6 functional ACs passing + dev agent's test report.","newString":"- **AC7 indirect:** Test source files not shipped in npm package, so vitest/bats couldn't run in container. Verified indirectly via all 6 functional ACs passing + dev agent's test report.\n\n### 8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability — create-story (2026-03-23T08:35Z)\n\n- **Risk: Semgrep Rust pattern matching for match arms and closures can be finicky.** AC2 and AC3 depend on this — dev agent should validate rules carefully.\n- **Risk: AC4 tagged integration-required** — verifying `codeharness audit` picks up Rust rules requires a real Rust project with Semgrep installed.\n- **Observation: Pure-config story** — no TypeScript changes, just 3 YAML files. Clean scope.\n- **Observation: computeSummary() rule-name mismatch** — existing analyzer.ts hardcodes JS/TS rule names. New Rust rule IDs won't match, so summary percentages will be off for Rust projects. Outside story scope but a follow-up candidate.","originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 5)\n\n### 8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding — create-story (2026-03-23T12:14Z)\n\n- **Observation: ACs 1-3 are already implemented.** Code for `getStackLabel('rust')`, `getCoverageTool('rust')`, and the Rust branch in `generateAgentsMdContent()` was added in earlier stories. Only AC4 (`getProjectName` Cargo.toml parsing) is new work.\n- **Risk: Cargo.toml parsing edge cases.** Simple regex parsing without a TOML parser could break on comments, inline tables, or multi-line strings. Known tradeoff per NFR4.\n- **Workaround: sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent.** Had to manually update status to `ready-for-dev`.\n\n### 8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding — dev-story (2026-03-23T12:18Z)\n\nNo issues reported. All 28 docs-scaffold tests pass, 3018/3018 vitest tests pass, 307/307 BATS tests pass. Clean implementation.\n\n### 8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding — code-review (2026-03-23T12:25Z)\n\n- **HIGH: Cargo.toml regex only matched double-quoted values.** Single quotes are valid TOML. Fixed to support both.\n- **HIGH: Cargo.toml section regex broke on `[` in values.** Fixed to use `[\\s\\S]*?` with lookahead for next section.\n- **HIGH: Missing showboat proof document.** Created.\n- **MEDIUM: Test assertion too weak** for dependencies-only Cargo.toml. Fixed to verify actual fallback value.\n- **MEDIUM: No test for `[package]` section with no `name` field.** Added.\n- **LOW (not fixed): Mixed quote regex doesn't enforce matching quotes** — acceptable for simple parser per NFR3.\n- **LOW (not fixed): Pre-existing uncovered lines 180, 221-222** in docs-scaffold.ts (unrelated to 8-8).\n\n### 8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding — verification (2026-03-23T12:30Z)\n\n- All 7 ACs passed. Verifier used a Node.js script (`verify-acs.mjs`) to import and test the functions directly from the dist bundle — creative approach.\n- **OBSERVABILITY GAP on all ACs:** No log events detected for any of the docs-scaffold function calls. These are pure utility functions with no instrumentation — expected for documentation scaffolding.\n- **AC7 indirect:** Test source files not shipped in npm package, so vitest/bats couldn't run in container. Verified indirectly via all 6 functional ACs passing + dev agent's test report.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":25,"oldLines":3,"newStart":25,"newLines":10,"lines":[" - All 7 ACs passed. Verifier used a Node.js script (`verify-acs.mjs`) to import and test the functions directly from the dist bundle — creative approach."," - **OBSERVABILITY GAP on all ACs:** No log events detected for any of the docs-scaffold function calls. These are pure utility functions with no instrumentation — expected for documentation scaffolding."," - **AC7 indirect:** Test source files not shipped in npm package, so vitest/bats couldn't run in container. Verified indirectly via all 6 functional ACs passing + dev agent's test report.","+","+### 8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability — create-story (2026-03-23T08:35Z)","+","+- **Risk: Semgrep Rust pattern matching for match arms and closures can be finicky.** AC2 and AC3 depend on this — dev agent should validate rules carefully.","+- **Risk: AC4 tagged integration-required** — verifying `codeharness audit` picks up Rust rules requires a real Rust project with Semgrep installed.","+- **Observation: Pure-config story** — no TypeScript changes, just 3 YAML files. Clean scope.","+- **Observation: computeSummary() rule-name mismatch** — existing analyzer.ts hardcodes JS/TS rule names. New Rust rule IDs won't match, so summary percentages will be off for Rust projects. Outside story scope but a follow-up candidate."]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
