{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Y5Vmp4wHswe3FNr3ap85bX","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 3068 tests pass across 114 test files. Zero regressions.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nStory 8-9 implemented. Created 3 Semgrep YAML rules for Rust observability gap detection targeting the `tracing` crate:\n\n**Files created:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/patches/observability/rust-function-no-tracing.yaml` -- detects `fn`/`pub fn`/`async fn`/`pub async fn` without tracing macros or `#[instrument]`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/patches/observability/rust-catch-without-tracing.yaml` -- detects `Err($E) => { ... }` match arms without tracing\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/patches/observability/rust-error-path-no-tracing.yaml` -- detects `.map_err()` and `.unwrap_or_else()` closures without tracing\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/patches/observability/rust-function-no-tracing.rs` -- Semgrep test fixture\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/patches/observability/rust-catch-without-tracing.rs` -- Semgrep test fixture\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/patches/observability/rust-error-path-no-tracing.rs` -- Semgrep test fixture\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/observability/__tests__/rust-semgrep-rules.test.ts` -- 47 vitest tests\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/docs/exec-plans/active/8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability.md`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/docs/exec-plans/active/8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability.proof.md`\n\n**Files modified:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/patches/observability/AGENTS.md` -- added Rust rules/fixtures to docs\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability.md` -- status set to `review`, tasks checked off\n\n**Test results:** 3068 passed / 114 files (was 3021 / 113). Zero regressions.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Semgrep validation broken locally:** `semgrep --validate` crashes with `Bigarray.create: negative dimension` on semgrep-core 1.136.0 on this macOS. Confirmed it crashes on existing JS/TS rules too -- system-wide issue, not rule-specific. Structural validation done via YAML parsing in vitest. CI should validate successfully.\n- **computeSummary won't count Rust rule IDs:** The `matchesRule()` function in `analyzer.ts` only recognizes `function-no-debug-log`, `catch-without-logging`, and `error-path-no-log` (JS/TS names). Rust rule IDs like `rust-function-no-tracing` won't be counted as function gaps or error handler gaps in summary stats. The `levelDistribution` still works. This is an architectural limitation -- a future story should add the Rust rule names to `matchesRule()` or make it more generic. Per story scope (\"No TypeScript Code Changes Required\"), this was left as-is.\n- **Large rule file:** `rust-function-no-tracing.yaml` is ~230 lines due to combinatorial explosion of 4 function forms x 10 tracing macros + 8 instrument attribute exclusions. Within the 300-line NFR1 limit but verbose. Semgrep's pattern language doesn't support wildcard matching across visibility/async modifiers, so the repetition is unavoidable."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: afe2889436ec4264e (use SendMessage with to: 'afe2889436ec4264e' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 68941\ntool_uses: 67\nduration_ms: 439236</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9d3ab825-6dfa-42d3-92d1-28b7bc09852d","uuid":"e66cab93-9387-4df7-8c7f-2525f2ddfef8","timestamp":"2026-03-23T08:43:27.829Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability.md — implement all tasks, write tests, and mark the story for review. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously through all tasks until complete. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do