{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01XhhUsicQzFgTzayFy5sqeK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_012xaPNCWZuZeLDwNAzfXR4k","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","old_string":"- **Observation: computeSummary() rule-name mismatch** — existing analyzer.ts hardcodes JS/TS rule names. New Rust rule IDs won't match, so summary percentages will be off for Rust projects. Outside story scope but a follow-up candidate.","new_string":"- **Observation: computeSummary() rule-name mismatch** — existing analyzer.ts hardcodes JS/TS rule names. New Rust rule IDs won't match, so summary percentages will be off for Rust projects. Outside story scope but a follow-up candidate.\n\n### 8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability — dev-story (2026-03-23T08:43Z)\n\n- **Semgrep validation broken locally:** `semgrep --validate` crashes with `Bigarray.create: negative dimension` on semgrep-core 1.136.0 on macOS. System-wide issue, not rule-specific. Structural validation done via YAML parsing in vitest.\n- **computeSummary won't count Rust rule IDs:** `matchesRule()` in analyzer.ts only recognizes JS/TS rule names. Rust rule IDs won't be counted in summary stats. Architectural limitation — future story needed.\n- **Large rule file:** `rust-function-no-tracing.yaml` is ~230 lines due to combinatorial explosion. Within NFR1 limit but verbose. Semgrep doesn't support wildcard matching across visibility/async modifiers."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1388,"cache_read_input_tokens":44818,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1388},"output_tokens":63,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9d3ab825-6dfa