{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Gkgn1vTptEpQstxXEPyvGi","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# patches/observability/ — Semgrep Rules for Observability Gap Detection\n     2→\n     3→Standalone Semgrep YAML rules for static analysis of observability gaps. Each `.yaml` file is a complete Semgrep config — no build step, no TypeScript. Deleting a rule file removes that check.\n     4→\n     5→## Rules\n     6→\n     7→### JavaScript / TypeScript\n     8→\n     9→| File | Purpose | Severity |\n    10→|------|---------|----------|\n    11→| catch-without-logging.yaml | Detects catch blocks without error/warn logging | WARNING |\n    12→| function-no-debug-log.yaml | Detects functions without debug/info logging | INFO |\n    13→| error-path-no-log.yaml | Detects error paths (throw/return err) without preceding log | WARNING |\n    14→\n    15→### Rust\n    16→\n    17→| File | Purpose | Severity |\n    18→|------|---------|----------|\n    19→| rust-function-no-tracing.yaml | Detects Rust functions without tracing instrumentation | INFO |\n    20→| rust-catch-without-tracing.yaml | Detects Rust error match arms without tracing | WARNING |\n    21→| rust-error-path-no-tracing.yaml | Detects Rust error-path closures (map_err/unwrap_or_else) without tracing | WARNING |\n    22→\n    23→## Test Fixtures\n    24→\n    25→### JavaScript / TypeScript\n    26→\n    27→| File | Purpose |\n    28→|------|---------|\n    29→| catch-without-logging.ts | Test cases for catch-without-logging rule (annotated with `// ruleid:` / `// ok:`) |\n    30→| function-no-debug-log.ts | Test cases for function-no-debug-log rule |\n    31→| error-path-no-log.ts | Test cases for error-path-no-log rule |\n    32→\n    33→### Rust\n    34→\n    35→| File | Purpose |\n    36→|------|---------|\n    37→| rust-function-no-tracing.rs | Test cases for rust-function-no-tracing rule |\n    38→| rust-catch-without-tracing.rs | Test cases for rust-catch-without-tracing rule |\n    39→| rust-error-path-no-tracing.rs | Test cases for rust-error-path-no-tracing rule |\n    40→\n    41→## Testing\n    42→\n    43→Run `semgrep --test patches/observability/` to execute all test fixtures against their rules.\n    44→\n    45→## Customization\n    46→\n    47→Edit YAML rules to add custom logger patterns (e.g., `logger.error(...)` for winston). Rules use `pattern-not` / `pattern-not-inside` to detect absence of logging.\n    48→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MYevXB4Mt86CKSoLvU5eeE","session_id":"9d3ab825-6dfa-42d3-92d1-28b7bc09852d","uuid":"c235ec26-da80-4845-8848-81403f343032","timestamp":"2026-03-23T08:44:36.367Z"}
