{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DADCuAyMF3hCtXT7RWEDfS","type":"tool_result","content":"   195→- computeSummary's matchesRule() only recognizes JS/TS rule names — Rust rule IDs won't be counted in function/error-handler stats (level distribution still works). This is a known limitation that can be addressed in a future story.\n   196→\n   197→### File List\n   198→\n   199→- patches/observability/rust-function-no-tracing.yaml (CREATED)\n   200→- patches/observability/rust-catch-without-tracing.yaml (CREATED)\n   201→- patches/observability/rust-error-path-no-tracing.yaml (CREATED)\n   202→- patches/observability/rust-function-no-tracing.rs (CREATED)\n   203→- patches/observability/rust-catch-without-tracing.rs (CREATED)\n   204→- patches/observability/rust-error-path-no-tracing.rs (CREATED)\n   205→- patches/observability/AGENTS.md (MODIFIED)\n   206→- src/modules/observability/__tests__/rust-semgrep-rules.test.ts (CREATED)\n   207→- docs/exec-plans/active/8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability.md (CREATED)\n   208→- docs/exec-plans/active/8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability.proof.md (CREATED)\n   209→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MYevXB4Mt86CKSoLvU5eeE","session_id":"9d3ab825-6dfa-42d3-92d1-28b7bc09852d","uuid":"e762976a-5bf6-48ba-8f42-987f75969d62","timestamp":"2026-03-23T08:47:33.287Z"}
