{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MYevXB4Mt86CKSoLvU5eeE","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All green.\n\n---\n\n**Review Summary**\n\nStory 8-9 (Semgrep Rules for Rust Observability) passes adversarial review with one fix applied.\n\n**Files modified:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/patches/observability/rust-function-no-tracing.rs` -- Added `tracing::trace!()` namespaced test case (was missing, only bare `trace!()` was tested)\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/observability/__tests__/rust-semgrep-rules.test.ts` -- Added test assertion verifying both namespaced and bare `trace!` coverage in fixture (48 tests, up from 47)\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability.md` -- Status changed from `review` to `verifying`, review notes appended\n\n**Coverage:** 97.06% overall, all 123 files above 80% floor. 3069 tests pass, zero regressions.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and their severity:**\n- **HIGH (fixed):** Test fixture `rust-function-no-tracing.rs` was missing `tracing::trace!()` namespaced test case. The bare `trace!()` was covered but the namespaced form was not, meaning a regression in the `pattern-not` for `tracing::trace!()` would go undetected. Fixed by adding the case and a corresponding test assertion.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt):**\n- `rust-function-no-tracing.yaml` at 282 lines (93% of 300-line NFR1 limit) due to N*M pattern explosion. Correct for Semgrep semantics but could be refactored with `pattern-not-inside` in a future story.\n- `rust-catch-without-tracing.yaml` and `rust-error-path-no-tracing.yaml` only exclude `error!/warn!` levels, not `info!/debug!` in error paths. Matches JS/TS precedent and AC wording, but may cause false positives for devs who log errors at info level.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- `computeSummary()` in `analyzer.ts` does not recognize Rust rule IDs (`rust-function-no-tracing`, etc.). The `matchesRule()` function only has JS/TS constants. Rust gaps ARE detected and parsed correctly, but summary statistics (`totalFunctions`, `errorHandlersWithoutLogs`) will be 0 for Rust projects. `levelDistribution` works. Needs a follow-up story to add Rust rule ID constants -- story scope explicitly forbids modifying `analyzer.ts`.\n- `semgrep --validate` could not run locally (semgrep-core crash on macOS). YAML rules are validated structurally via tests but not by Semgrep's native validator. CI pipeline should cover this.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. The YAML-only approach with Semgrep auto-discovery is clean and well-isolated.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. Story approved with fix applied."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aec99d7f61fe0319c (use SendMessage with to: 'aec99d7f61fe0319c' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 54368\ntool_uses: 41\nduration_ms: 259215</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9d3ab825-6dfa-42d3-92d1-28b7bc09852d","uuid":"c4634c93-cead-4c39-9073-4283747791a8","timestamp":"2026-03-23T08:48:21.979Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file floor and the overall 90% target. Update the story status to `verifying` when all issues are fixed and coverage passes. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Bugs found and their severity (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW with brief description)\n- Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt)\n- Coverage gaps (files below floor, untested edge cases, areas needing integration tests)\n- Architecture concerns (patterns that don't fit, coupling issues, missing abstractions)\n- Items sent back for re-development (what failed and why)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"aec99d7f61fe0319c","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All green.\n\n---\n\n**Review Summary**\n\nStory 8-9 (Semgrep Rules for Rust Observability) passes adversarial review with one fix applied.\n\n**Files modified:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/patches/observability/rust-function-no-tracing.rs` -- Added `tracing::trace!()` namespaced test case (was missing, only bare `trace!()` was tested)\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/observability/__tests__/rust-semgrep-rules.test.ts` -- Added test assertion verifying both namespaced and bare `trace!` coverage in fixture (48 tests, up from 47)\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability.md` -- Status changed from `review` to `verifying`, review notes appended\n\n**Coverage:** 97.06% overall, all 123 files above 80% floor. 3069 tests pass, zero regressions.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and their severity:**\n- **HIGH (fixed):** Test fixture `rust-function-no-tracing.rs` was missing `tracing::trace!()` namespaced test case. The bare `trace!()` was covered but the namespaced form was not, meaning a regression in the `pattern-not` for `tracing::trace!()` would go undetected. Fixed by adding the case and a corresponding test assertion.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt):**\n- `rust-function-no-tracing.yaml` at 282 lines (93% of 300-line NFR1 limit) due to N*M pattern explosion. Correct for Semgrep semantics but could be refactored with `pattern-not-inside` in a future story.\n- `rust-catch-without-tracing.yaml` and `rust-error-path-no-tracing.yaml` only exclude `error!/warn!` levels, not `info!/debug!` in error paths. Matches JS/TS precedent and AC wording, but may cause false positives for devs who log errors at info level.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- `computeSummary()` in `analyzer.ts` does not recognize Rust rule IDs (`rust-function-no-tracing`, etc.). The `matchesRule()` function only has JS/TS constants. Rust gaps ARE detected and parsed correctly, but summary statistics (`totalFunctions`, `errorHandlersWithoutLogs`) will be 0 for Rust projects. `levelDistribution` works. Needs a follow-up story to add Rust rule ID constants -- story scope explicitly forbids modifying `analyzer.ts`.\n- `semgrep --validate` could not run locally (semgrep-core crash on macOS). YAML rules are validated structurally via tests but not by Semgrep's native validator. CI pipeline should cover this.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. The YAML-only approach with Semgrep auto-discovery is clean and well-isolated.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. Story approved with fix applied."}],"totalDurationMs":259215,"totalTokens":54368,"totalToolUseCount":41,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":253,"cache_read_input_tokens":53341,"output_tokens":773,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":253},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
