{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Y4zAc2vUU9mcPVU9pnta3h","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01C5XoengkXWvSS6k7BXPyrV","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","old_string":"- **Large rule file:** `rust-function-no-tracing.yaml` is ~230 lines due to combinatorial explosion. Within NFR1 limit but verbose. Semgrep doesn't support wildcard matching across visibility/async modifiers.","new_string":"- **Large rule file:** `rust-function-no-tracing.yaml` is ~230 lines due to combinatorial explosion. Within NFR1 limit but verbose. Semgrep doesn't support wildcard matching across visibility/async modifiers.\n\n### 8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability — code-review (2026-03-23T08:48Z)\n\n- **HIGH (fixed):** Test fixture missing `tracing::trace!()` namespaced test case. Only bare `trace!()` was tested — a regression in `pattern-not` for namespaced form would go undetected. Fixed.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `rust-function-no-tracing.yaml` at 282 lines (93% of NFR1 limit) due to N*M pattern explosion. Could be refactored with `pattern-not-inside` in future.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Error path rules only exclude `error!/warn!` levels, not `info!/debug!`. Matches JS/TS precedent but may cause false positives for devs logging errors at info level.\n- **Coverage gap:** `computeSummary()` won't recognize Rust rule IDs — follow-up story needed."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1842,"cache_read_input_tokens":48817,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1842},"output_tokens":65,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9d3ab825-6dfa-42d3-92d1-28b7bc09852d","uuid":"492f8c8d-2515-4509-966a-3bf