{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01HHwynW89tL9FUCzcvCU89N","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_011N91gSDarV8R1SJAmKUGEA","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cd /tmp/codeharness-verify-8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability && claude --print --max-budget-usd 5 --allowedTools Bash Read Write Glob Grep Edit -p \"You are a black-box verifier. Your job is to verify that a software feature works correctly from the user's perspective — using ONLY the installed CLI, documentation, and observability data. You have NO access to source code.\n\n## Why Black-Box Verification\n\nThis workspace contains NO source code. The src/ directory does not exist. This is intentional — you must verify the feature works as a user would experience it, not by reading implementation details.\n\n## Step 1: Read README.md\n\nStart by reading README.md in this workspace.\n\n## Step 2: Review Acceptance Criteria\n\nThe story file story.md contains the acceptance criteria you must verify. Read it.\n\n## Step 3: Verify Each AC\n\nFor EACH acceptance criterion:\n1. Run commands inside the Docker container via docker exec codeharness-verify ...\n2. Capture the command output as evidence\n3. Query observability endpoints if runtime evidence is needed\n\n### Docker Container\n\n- Container name: codeharness-verify\n- ALL CLI commands MUST run via: docker exec codeharness-verify <command>\n- The Semgrep rules are at: /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/patches/observability/\n- The .rs test fixtures are in the same directory\n- semgrep is installed in the container\n\n### Verification Strategy for Semgrep Rules\n\nFor AC1, AC2, AC3: Create sample Rust files inside the container that should trigger each rule, then run semgrep against them:\n  docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cat > /tmp/test.rs << EOF\n  fn untraced_function() { let x = 1; }\n  EOF'\n  docker exec codeharness-verify semgrep scan --config /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/patches/observability/rust-function-no-tracing.yaml /tmp/test.rs\n\nAlso test with the .rs fixture files in the patches directory to verify both positive and negative cases.\n\nFor AC4: Run docker exec codeharness-verify codeharness audit --help to check if audit command exists, then create a minimal Rust project and run the audit to see if Semgrep discovers the Rust rules. If codeharness audit requires a full project setup, test the auto-discovery by running semgrep scan --config /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/patches/observability/ on a .rs file — since Semgrep auto-discovers by languages field, the Rust rules should match Rust files and JS/TS rules should be ignored.\n\nFor AC5: Run docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness && npm test 2>&1 | tail -20' OR verify that the npm package is installed and functional. Since this is a black-box verify, checking that the package loads correctly via docker exec codeharness-verify node -e \\\"require('codeharness')\\\" may be sufficient.\n\n### Observability Endpoints (query from HOST)\n\n- VictoriaLogs: http://localhost:9428\n- VictoriaMetrics: http://localhost:8428\n- VictoriaTraces: http://localhost:16686\n\nAfter EACH docker exec command, query: curl 'http://localhost:9428/select/logsql/query?query=_stream_id:*&start=-30s&limit=100'\n\n## Step 4: Write Proof Document\n\nWrite your verification proof to: verification/8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability-proof.md\n\nUse this format for each AC:\n\n## AC N: <description>\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify <command>\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n\\`\\`\\`output\n<actual output>\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**IMPORTANT: Only use bash and output as code fence languages.** Never use bare fences without a language tag. Showboat will try to execute any unlabeled code block.\n\n## Critical Rules\n\n1. ALL commands MUST use docker exec codeharness-verify — do NOT run commands directly on the host.\n2. Do NOT attempt to access source code — there is no src/ directory.\n3. Report REAL failures — if a feature does not work, report that as a failure.\n4. Every AC needs functional evidence — reading docs alone is not evidence.\n5. [ESCALATE] is ONLY for things that are genuinely impossible to automate.\n6. Never switch to unit-testable verification.\" 2>&1","description":"Run black-box verifier session","timeout":300000},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1068,"cache_read_input_tokens":61976,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1068},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9d3ab825-6dfa-42d3-92d1-28b7bc09852d","uuid":"cc67b8b8-423c-4b85-bf18-b8d5eed2dbde"}
