{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011N91gSDarV8R1SJAmKUGEA","type":"tool_result","content":"Warning: no stdin data received in 3s, proceeding without it. If piping from a slow command, redirect stdin explicitly: < /dev/null to skip, or wait longer.\n## Verification Complete\n\n**Overall: FAIL**\n\n| AC | Result |\n|----|--------|\n| AC1 | **PASS** — rust-function-no-tracing detects 4/4 positive cases, excludes 12/12 negative cases |\n| AC2 | **FAIL** — rust-catch-without-tracing has invalid pattern syntax (`Err($E) => { ... }` causes `Stdlib.Parsing.Parse_error`). Zero findings on any input. |\n| AC3 | **PASS** — rust-error-path-no-tracing detects 2/2 positive cases, excludes 8/8 negative cases |\n| AC4 | **PASS** — Semgrep auto-discovers 3 Rust rules from 6 total when scanning .rs files |\n| AC5 | **PARTIAL** — CLI works (v0.23.1), test suite not shipped in npm package |\n\n**Root cause of AC2 failure:** Match arms (`Err($E) => { ... }`) are not standalone expressions in Rust — they only exist inside `match` blocks. Semgrep's Rust parser cannot parse this pattern. The dev agent never caught this because Semgrep crashed on macOS and they relied on YAML-level unit tests only.\n\nProof document written to `verification/8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability-proof.md`.\nShell cwd was reset to /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9d3ab825-6dfa-42d3-92d1-28b7bc09852d","uuid":"57c3f9f8-d2d4-4345-b5d1-fe8b88982c3a","timestamp":"2026-03-23T08:53:45.856Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"Warning: no stdin data received in 3s, proceeding without it. If piping from a slow command, redirect stdin explicitly: < /dev/null to skip, or wait longer.\n## Verification Complete\n\n**Overall: FAIL**\n\n| AC | Result |\n|----|--------|\n| AC1 | **PASS** — rust-function-no-tracing detects 4/4 positive cases, excludes 12/12 negative cases |\n| AC2 | **FAIL** — rust-catch-without-tracing has invalid pattern syntax (`Err($E) => { ... }` causes `Stdlib.Parsing.Parse_error`). Zero findings on any input. |\n| AC3 | **PASS** — rust-error-path-no-tracing detects 2/2 positive cases, excludes 8/8 negative cases |\n| AC4 | **PASS** — Semgrep auto-discovers 3 Rust rules from 6 total when scanning .rs files |\n| AC5 | **PARTIAL** — CLI works (v0.23.1), test suite not shipped in npm package |\n\n**Root cause of AC2 failure:** Match arms (`Err($E) => { ... }`) are not standalone expressions in Rust — they only exist inside `match` blocks. Semgrep's Rust parser cannot parse this pattern. The dev agent never caught this because Semgrep crashed on macOS and they relied on YAML-level unit tests only.\n\nProof document written to `verification/8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability-proof.md`.","stderr":"\nShell cwd was reset to /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
