{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01BsbBrPwsarVT12Rsrav8ZQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01HZXyQFRUZUi2HM3YEHKFmg","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","old_string":"- **Coverage gap:** `computeSummary()` won't recognize Rust rule IDs — follow-up story needed.","new_string":"- **Coverage gap:** `computeSummary()` won't recognize Rust rule IDs — follow-up story needed.\n\n### 8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability — verification (2026-03-23T08:54Z)\n\n- **AC2 FAIL:** `rust-catch-without-tracing.yaml` has invalid Rust pattern syntax. `Err($E) => { ... }` is not a standalone expression — match arms only exist inside `match` blocks. Semgrep parse error: `Stdlib.Parsing.Parse_error`. Zero findings on any input.\n- **Root cause:** Dev agent couldn't run `semgrep --validate` locally (macOS Bigarray crash). Relied on YAML-parsing unit tests which don't validate Semgrep pattern syntax.\n- **Fix needed:** Wrap match arm patterns inside full `match` expressions, e.g. `match $X { Err($E) => { ... } }` or use `pattern-inside` with a `match` block.\n- **AC1, AC3, AC4 PASS.** AC5 partial (tests not shipped in container, CLI functional).\n- Story returned to `in-progress` for AC2 fix."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":163,"cache_read_input_tokens":71234,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":163},"output_tokens":71,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9d3ab825-6dfa-42d3-92d1-28b7bc09852d","uuid":"fb9ccc3d-e684-404e-b1c2-ec65128427f4"}
